<h3>Support the Atlas</h3>

<p>The Global Adaptation Atlas aims to respond to the diversity and complexity of information required to conduct research, identify opportunities for, act on and evaluate adaptation efforts. The Atlas is the largest visual repository of the results of studies focused on the human impacts of climate change. It also is the first effort to dynamically combine both the science and practice of adaptation &mdash; allowing for a unique view of the past, current and expected impacts and the proposed responses. </p>
<p>We have built the Atlas in hopes that it can serve multiple purposes &mdash; including, but not limited to: </p>
<ol type="i">

	<li>As a priority-setting tool for action based on the current and projected impacts of climate change</li>
	<li>As a research-agenda setting tool </li>
	<li>A planning tool for local, regional and national actors</li>
	<li>A data resource for researchers and others interested in pursuing further work in this area</li>
	<li>A method of monitoring and evaluating adaptation activities</li>
	<li>A repository of information on past, current and planned adaptation activities, including the ability to contact other professionals working in this field</li>
</ol>

Due to the diversity of the information and applications of the Atlas, we envision that there are several avenues for collaboration, partnership and financial and in-kind support. 
