<h4 class="bar"><a name="collaborate">Collaborate </a></h4>
<p>The Atlas team welcomes opportunities to collaborate with interested individuals and parties that work in or areas related to adaptation. We rely extensively on our diverse set of partners and collaborators to stay engaged and relevant in the adaptation community as well as for the most current information on adaptation activities and scientific studies on the human impacts of climate change. </p>
<p>More specifically, we look to partner with organizations that are:</p>
<ol type="i">
	<li>Funding and implementing adaptation strategies and activities,</li>
	<li>Conducting research and publishing studies on the human impacts of climate change,</li>
	<li>Engaging in the debate through organization of or participating in initiatives that are related to creating frameworks for the design, implementation and evaluation of adaptation activities.</li>
</ol>
A list of our current partners can be found <a href="partners.cfm">here</a>.
We encourage you to get in touch with us through our contact form or by e-mailing us at <a href="mailto:partners@adaptationatlas.org">partners@adaptationatlas.org </a>. Please do not hesitate to contact us even if your initiative does not directly fall under the above categories. We appreciate any and all interest in the Adaptation Atlas and look forward to working with you. 
