<p>To continue the development of the Global Adaptation Atlas &mdash; to expand and enhance its scope in theme and scale, to pilot its use and to establish a wider-reaching network of partners, we require a substantial amount of continued funding and support. We envision that contributions can support the overall operations of the initiative or particular 'parts and efforts' of the Atlas:</p>
	<ol type="i">
	<li><strong>Thematic approach</strong>: Organizations and individuals that are interested in our themes of food, health, land, livelihood and water can support the continued development of the Atlas in those particular sectors &mdash; including the visualization of uncertainty and vulnerability data. </li>
	<li><strong>Regional or Country Pilot</strong>: The team is looking for partners to pilot the use of the Atlas as a planning and monitoring tool in a single country or region. We envision that this exercise will test the power of the Atlas and provide feedback for the implementing country as well as fuel further innovation of the Adaptation Atlas. </li>
	<li><strong>Outreach/ Network Building</strong>: The applicability and relevancy of the Atlas depends on our ability to reach the communities that are active in the adaptation field. Moreover, the Atlas concept relies upon the continued engagement and participation of a wide variety of partners who are essential in enhancing, applying and supplying vital information to the Atlas. </li>
	</ol>
<p>The Global Adaptation Atlas team welcomes any opportunity to discuss the next phases of development of the Atlas prototype, as well as our need for continued financial support in making this initiative a success. </p>
<p>Please contact Nisha Krishnan, the Global Adaptation Atlas Project Manager at <a href="mailto:Krishnan@adaptationatlas.org">Krishnan@adaptationatlas.org</a> for further information on the project and how you can help. </p>
